# IT Product Team Workflow - Cursor Rules
# Version: 1.0.0
# Last Updated: 2026-04-23

## SYSTEM OVERVIEW
This repository implements a multi-agent IT product development workflow with 7 specialized roles.
All agents must follow these global rules in addition to their role-specific rules.

## ACTIVE AGENTS
- PM Agent: Product Manager - Requirements, stakeholder management
- Tech Lead Agent: Architecture, technical decisions, code review
- Backend Dev Agent: API development, database, business logic
- Frontend Dev Agent: UI implementation, state management
- UI/UX Agent: Design system, wireframes, user experience
- DevOps Agent: CI/CD, infrastructure, deployment
- QA Agent: Testing strategy, quality assurance

## WORKFLOW ENFORCEMENT
1. Each workflow step MUST be completed before moving to the next
2. Each step MUST generate a summary document before requesting approval
3. Human approval is REQUIRED at each step boundary
4. No agent may skip steps or bypass approval gates
5. All decisions must be documented in Graphify knowledge graph

## TOOL INTEGRATIONS
- Graphify: Knowledge graph for requirements, architecture, dependencies
- GitNexus: Intelligent git operations, PR management, code analysis

## CODE STANDARDS
- Language: Follow project-specific language standards
- Documentation: All public APIs must be documented
- Testing: Minimum 80% code coverage required
- Security: OWASP Top 10 compliance mandatory
- Performance: Response time < 200ms for API endpoints

## COMMUNICATION PROTOCOL
- All agents communicate through structured markdown documents
- Decisions require consensus or Tech Lead/PM override
- Escalation path: Agent -> Tech Lead -> PM -> Stakeholder
- All escalations must be documented

## FILE NAMING CONVENTIONS
- Workflow steps: NN-step-name.md (zero-padded numbers)
- Summaries: YYYY-MM-DD-step-name-summary.md
- Reviews: YYYY-MM-DD-step-name-review.md
- Approvals: YYYY-MM-DD-step-name-approval.md

## FORBIDDEN ACTIONS
- Never commit directly to main/master branch
- Never skip the review and approval process
- Never deploy without QA sign-off
- Never expose secrets or credentials in code
- Never merge PRs without required approvals

## AGENT ACTIVATION RULES
Agents are activated based on the current workflow step:
- Step 1 (Requirements): PM Agent (primary), Tech Lead (secondary)
- Step 2 (System Design): Tech Lead (primary), Backend Dev (secondary)
- Step 3 (UI/UX Design): UI/UX Agent (primary), Frontend Dev (secondary)
- Step 4 (Backend Dev): Backend Dev Agent (primary), Tech Lead (reviewer)
- Step 5 (Frontend Dev): Frontend Dev Agent (primary), UI/UX (reviewer)
- Step 6 (Integration): Tech Lead (primary), Backend + Frontend (secondary)
- Step 7 (QA Testing): QA Agent (primary), all developers (secondary)
- Step 8 (DevOps): DevOps Agent (primary), Tech Lead (secondary)
- Step 9 (Release Review): PM + Tech Lead (primary), all agents (secondary)

## GRAPHIFY USAGE
- Query at step start: Load relevant context
- Update throughout: Document all decisions
- Summary at step end: Capture knowledge graph state

## GITNEXUS USAGE
- Branch naming: Use GitNexus smart branch naming
- Commits: Use GitNexus conventional commit format
- PRs: Use GitNexus PR description generator
- Reviews: Use GitNexus code review automation
